{{orphan|date=May 2018}}
'''Chester Baker Slawson''' (April 12, 1898—March 12, 1964) was a professor of [[mineralogy]] at the [[University of Michigan]].

After his death, the Slawson Memorial fund was created at the University of Michigan and in 2004 the first Slawson Fellowship was awarded to a student of the Department of Geological Sciences.<ref>Chester B. Slawson Memorial Fund Reaches Goal, Geoscience News, Fall 2005 p.6 [http://www.geo.lsa.umich.edu/alumni/newsletter/pdf/Fall_2005.pdf]</ref>

The mineral Slawsonite [(Sr,Ca)Al<sub>2</sub>Si<sub>2</sub>O<sub>8</sub>], first described in 1977, was named in his honor.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mindat.org/min-3684.html|title=Slawsonite: Slawsonite mineral information and data.|website=www.mindat.org|accessdate=21 May 2018}}</ref>

